  "pr_number": 283,
  "issue_number": 270,
  "issue_title": "Feature: add screen understanding cards",
  "issue_body": "## Problem\nTouchPilot already has local screen summaries and suggested actions, but they are not surfaced as clear product UI cards. Users need to see what the app understood before trusting suggested actions.\n\n## Proposed behavior\nAdd visible screen-understanding cards that present the current screen summary and suggested actions from existing local ScreenContext/Summary logic.\n\n## Goal to reach\nWhen the user asks about the current screen or opens the relevant UI surface, TouchPilot shows a clear card with what it sees and useful local actions.\n\n## Minimal scope\n- Reuse existing ScreenContext and ScreenSummary logic.\n- Show summary text in a card.\n- Show a small capped list of suggested actions.\n- Keep suggestions descriptive unless the user explicitly chooses/runs one.\n- Handle empty or weak context with a clear local-only fallback message.\n\n## Out of scope\n- New model training.\n- New Android control tools.\n- OCR/VLM implementation.\n- Replacing existing chat/tool execution cards.\n\n## User workflow\nA user can ask what is on screen and see a structured local summary plus safe suggested next actions.\n\n## Local-first impact\nThis makes existing local screen understanding visible without cloud inference.\n\n## Safety and security considerations\nCards must use redacted/display-safe screen text and must not expose sensitive fields.",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-16T03:25:04.000Z",
